extends layout

block content
	.span-24
		h2 Bookmarking help.
	.span-8
		p
			Most newsletter items come from these sources:
			br
			a(href="http://giles-posters.livejournal.com/friends") Giles-posters friends list
			br
			a(href="http://www.fanfiction.net/tv/Buffy_The_Vampire_Slayer/10/0/1/1/0/226/0/0/0/1/") FF.net stories with Giles
			br
		p Scan those sources for items of interest to Giles fans and 
			a(href="http://pinboard.in/howto/#saving") bookmark
			|  them on 
			a(href="http://pinboard.in") Pinboard.
			|  You should be logged into the 
			a(href="http://pinboard.in/u:#{account}")= account
			|  Pinboard account.
		p The 
			i title
			| should be the title and chapter number for fic and fanart, the title for contests or ficathons, or any other clear name for the item. The <i>description</i> should contain information such as the pairing and rating of a fic, whether a piece of fanart is worksafe, or if any warnings apply.
		p Each item needs at least two tags: one to identify the poster or community the item comes from, and one to specify to which category the item belongs in the newsletter.
	.span-16.last
		.span-8
			h3 Source tags
			.span-4
				| Livejournal poster
				br
				| Livejournal community
				br
				| Dreamwidth poster
				br
				| Dreamwidth community
				br
				| AO3 pseudonym
				br
				| Insanejournal poster
				br
				| Insanejournal community
			.span-4.last
				span.example poster:
					i username
				br
				span.example comm:
					i commname
				br
				span.example dwposter:
					i username
				br
				span.example dwcomm:
					i commname
				br
				span.example ao3:
					i pseud
				br
				span.example ijposter:
					i username
				br
				span.example ijcomm:
					i commname
				br
		.span-8.last
			h3 Category tags
			.span-4
				- each tag in order
					= categories[tag]
					br
			.span-4.last
				- each tag in order
					span.example cat:#{tag}
					br
		.span-16.last(style="padding-top: 2em")
			h3 Series tags
			p Items in a series, such as a multi-chapter fic, can be connected into a single entry in  the newsletter by a 
				span.example series: 
				| tag. Invent a meaningful  tag for each series. Use one word from the title or join multiple 
				| words together with hyphens. (Pinboard tags can't have spaces in them.) Examples:
			p
				span.example series:teatime
				br
				span.example series:band-candy
				br
				span.example series:giles-is-awesome
				br
			p Create series pinboard bookmarks in the order you want them to appear in the newsletter. 
				| That is, if you want chapters 5, 6, and 7 of a series to appear in the newsletter, 
				| bookmark chapter 5 first, then chapter 6, and so on.
	.span-24
		p: a.emphasized(href="/") &lt; Return to newsletter generator.
